7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1016, L.D. 1558, “Resolve, Establishing
10 the Commission to Update Maine's Public Policy on Higher Education”
11 Amend the resolve by inserting after the title the following:
12 'Emergency preamble. Whereas, acts and resolves of the Legislature do not
13 become effective until 90 days after adjournment unless enacted as emergencies; and
14 Whereas, this legislation establishes the Commission to Update Maine's Public Policy
15 on Higher Education; and
16 Whereas, this legislation must take effect before the expiration of the 90-day period
17 so that the commission may timely meet and make its report to the Legislature by
18 November 4, 2026; and
19 Whereas, in the judgment of the Legislature, these facts create an emergency within
20 the meaning of the Constitution of Maine and require the following legislation as
21 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health and safety; now,
22 therefore, be it'
23 Amend the resolve by striking out all of section 2 and inserting the following:
24 'Sec. 2. Commission membership. Resolved: That, notwithstanding Joint Rule
25 353, the commission consists of 14 members, including:
26 1. Two members of the Senate, appointed by the President of the Senate, who serve
27 on the Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs, including one member
28 of the party holding the largest number of seats in the Legislature and one member of the
29 party holding the 2nd largest number of seats in the Legislature;
30 2. Two members of the House of Representatives, appointed by the Speaker of the
31 House, who serve on the Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs,
32 including one member of the party holding the largest number of seats in the Legislature
33 and one member of the party holding the 2nd largest number of seats in the Legislature;
Page 1 - 132LR1869(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1016, L.D. 1558
1 3. One member who is a representative of a union representing the faculty of the Maine
2 Community College System, the University of Maine System or the Maine Maritime
3 Academy, appointed by the President of the Senate, as recommended by the Maine
4 Education Association Board of Directors;
5 4. One member representing the Certification and Higher Education Committee of the
6 State Board of Education, appointed by the President of the Senate, as recommended by
7 the Chair of the State Board of Education;
8 5. One member representing private colleges and universities in the State, appointed
9 by the Speaker of the House, as recommended by the Maine Independent Colleges
10 Association;
11 6. The Chancellor of the University of Maine System or the chancellor's designee;
12 7. The Chair of the University of Maine System Board of Trustees or the chair's
13 designee;
14 8. The President of the Maine Community College System or the president's designee;
15 9. The Chair of the Maine Community College System Board of Trustees or the chair's
16 designee;
17 10. The Chair of the Maine Maritime Academy Board of Trustees or the chair's
18 designee;
19 11. The President of the Maine Maritime Academy or the president's designee; and
20 12. The Commissioner of Education or the commissioner's designee.
21 In appointing members of the commission, the appointing authorities shall give
22 consideration to race, gender, socioeconomic diversity and geographic diversity.'
23 Amend the resolve in section 4 in the first line (page 1, line 39 in L.D.) by inserting
24 after the following: "commission" the following: '; number of meetings'
25 Amend the resolve in section 4 in the last line (page 2, line 6 in L.D.) by inserting after
26 the following: "business." the following: 'The commission may not meet more than 8 times.'
27 Amend the resolve by striking out all of section 7 and inserting the following:
28 'Sec. 7. Report. Resolved: That, notwithstanding Joint Rule 353, no later than
29 November 4, 2026, the commission shall submit a report that includes its findings and
30 recommendations, including suggested legislation, to the joint standing committee of the
31 Legislature having jurisdiction over education matters. The joint standing committee may
32 report out a bill related to the report to the 133rd Legislature in 2027.'
33 Amend the resolve by adding before the summary the following:
34 'Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
35 takes effect when approved.'
36 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
37 section number to read consecutively.
