COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1016, L.D. 1558
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment makes the following changes to the Commission to Update Maine's
33 Public Policy on Higher Education.
4 1. It changes the membership from 17 members to 14 members as follows:
5 A. It changes the membership from 3 members of the House of Representatives to 2
6 members;
7 B. It removes a member with expertise in higher education policy issues representing
8 a statewide education policy research institute;
9 C. It removes a member who is employed as a faculty member at a private college or
10 university in the State;
11 D. It removes a member who is a representative of a union representing the faculty of
12 the University of Maine System;
13 E. It removes a member who is a representative of a union representing the faculty of
14 the Maine Maritime Academy;
15 F. It removes a member who is currently enrolled as a student at a college or university
16 in the State; and
17 G. It adds 3 members, one member each from the board of trustees of the University
18 of Maine System, the Maine Community College System and the Maine Maritime
19 Academy.
20 2. It requires that certain appointments must be recommended by specific
21 organizations.
22 3. It specifies that the commission may meet no more than 8 times.
23 4. It changes the reporting date from December 3, 2025 to November 4, 2026.
24 5. It adds an emergency preamble and emergency clause.
